<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-11471] Unable to update the cron details from Quartz scheduler MBean</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-11471</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On Karaf container, if you try to change the cron expression in a camel-quartz2 endpoint (like below) from a JMX console such as hawtio, update fails to persist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-xml&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;route&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;from uri=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;quartz2://myGroup/myTimer?cron=0/1 * * * * ?&quot;&lt;/span&gt; /&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
      [...]
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;/route&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s because Quartz2 requires runtime dependency back to &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.camel.component.quartz2&lt;/tt&gt; but the default quartz bundle (of course) doesn&apos;t have it in &lt;tt&gt;Import-Package&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
